Popular Nigerian comedian AY Makun and his wife Mabel have welcomed a baby thirteen years after their first child. The comedian took to his Instagram page on Tuesday, January 18, 2022, where he shared a video of his wife and their newborn baby. “Our prayers in the last 13 years has been answered. AYOMIDE thank you for making @realmabelmakun and I, Mummy and Daddy again,” he captioned the video. “Thank you for making Michelle a BIG SISTER. Thanks to everyone who kept us in their prayers and never stopped feeding us with positive vibes.” “Trust in the Lord with all your heart and lean not on your own understanding; in all your ways submit to him, and he will make your paths straight.” GOD’S TIME IS ALWAYS THE BEST” Congratulations to Makuns from all of us at Pulse. AY and Mabel got married in 2008. (Pulse.ng)  Nigerian comedian, Ayo Makun has shown off the interior and exterior of his exotic mansion.  AY and wife, Mabel Just days after buying multimillion naira cars for himself and his wife, popular Nigerian comedian Ayo Makun, better known as AY has now shared the inside and outside of his house reportedly… In "Entertainment" Popular Nigerian comedian Ayo Makun, known as AY took to Instagram to share a video on how he has just bought his wife Mabel Makun and himself two cars. The comedian made sure he wasn't left out in the 'car spree' as he also got himself a brand new car.… In "Entertainment" One of Nigeria's most successful comedians, Ayo Makun and his wife, Mabel, are celebrating their 11th wedding anniversary today November 29th. It is noteworthy that the couple got married in 2008 and they have a beautiful daughter together called Michelle. AY posted the family photo seen above of himself with his… In "Entertainment"